description: For sale: $198,500. Towering Norway Pines are the backdrop for this 2000+ sq. ft. ranch featuring a huge eat-in kitchen with center island. Very private master bedroom with adjoining bath (jet tub/separate shower) and a massive walk-in closet. Living room boasts custom front view windows, patio door to deck and a built-in gas log fireplace with sunken cabinet inserts on each side. Other features include a main level laundry, family room w/ patio door, wheelchair ramp, over sized two-stall garage, heated shop/storage building and so much more!

For sale: $209,900. Greetings!  You are invited to call with questions, to take a tour, or make an offer. 

This comfortable 3-4 bedroom family home is on 4.39 wooded acres in Britt,  9 miles N of Virginia.  Consider "Tall Pine" Road; 3 bedrooms, 2 baths, office, and full basement with plenty of room to relax.  Invite friends and family to gather in the upper 3-season sunroom with a free standing gas fireplace. 
There is plenty of covered parking for all your toys and tools.  Utilize a 2 stall, 24' x 28' newly shingled garage with attached 8' x 28' heated workshop and a 30' x 40' pole building on slab with 2-10' x 40' covered storage areas.  Also a storage shed/could be chicken coop, walking/4 wheeler/snowmobile trails, and garden space.  Extras, too.
The drilled well and septic are compliant. 
Virginia and MIB school bus pick up.  Drive to either end of Lake Vermilion or Giant's Ridge in a half hour, and have easy access to Big Aspen Ski Trail and Taconite Snowmobile Trails.

Bring your horses and/or cattle! Approximately 30 acres of pasture land is fenced and the balance is wooded. An automatic water feeder and a 14?x32? loafing shed is ready for the animals to enjoy. Trails abound and the land provides for plenty of hunting opportunities. 
Park your vehicles and toys inside the 26x48 pole shed with 14? side walls or under the 14x48 lean to. Use the additional 12x30 building as an office or as man cave. High Speed Internet is available.
Plenty of recreation options are nearby. Groomed snowmobile trails are approximately ¼ mile away, a great public beach is just 3 miles away as are several fishing lakes. Other recreation opportunities in the area include the Mesabi Bike Trail, Giants Ridge (skiing and golfing), BWCA, and more.
